01:12:37,886 --> 01:12:40,582
Okay, keep your
breath going.

999
01:12:43,392 --> 01:12:44,689
What?

1000
01:12:44,727 --> 01:12:47,161
- Miss Duke?
- Yes?

1001
01:12:48,630 --> 01:12:50,427
Waldo Taft.

1002
01:12:50,466 --> 01:12:52,161
What about him?

1003
01:12:52,201 --> 01:12:53,930
He's coming
to dinner tonight.

1004
01:12:53,969 --> 01:12:56,870
- Oh yeah.
- What does he like to eat?

1005
01:12:56,905 --> 01:13:00,238
Oh God, what about that...

1006
01:13:00,275 --> 01:13:03,767
is that salmon
still in the freezer?

1007
01:13:03,812 --> 01:13:06,178
Well, I'm not allowed
to throw anything out,

1008
01:13:06,215 --> 01:13:07,910
so it's still there.

1009
01:13:07,950 --> 01:13:11,909
Mm, then tell the chef
to poach that.

1010
01:13:11,954 --> 01:13:13,080
Ah!

1011
01:13:13,122 --> 01:13:16,091
That salmon's been here
longer than I have.

1012
01:13:16,125 --> 01:13:19,526
It'll be fine.

1013
01:13:19,561 --> 01:13:23,691
That salmon's leftover from
when Jesus fed the 5,000.

1014
01:13:23,732 --> 01:13:25,324
That's how old it is.

1015
01:13:25,367 --> 01:13:27,631
It'll be fine.

1016
01:13:32,107 --> 01:13:34,575
Try to open up
your lower back a little bit.

1017
01:13:34,610 --> 01:13:37,374
I'll tell the chef to poach it.

1018
01:13:42,851 --> 01:13:46,719
This Marine Conservation Project
seems very interesting,

1019
01:13:46,755 --> 01:13:49,622
but I don't see the annual
fiscal report anywhere.

1020
01:13:49,658 --> 01:13:51,319
It's late.

1021
01:13:51,360 --> 01:13:53,851
Well, no report, no money.

1022
01:13:59,001 --> 01:14:01,333
- What's this now?
- The AlDS research.

1023
01:14:01,370 --> 01:14:04,669
They've asked for
a 10% increase over the last year.

1024
01:14:04,706 --> 01:14:06,230
It's not unreasonable.

1025
01:14:06,275 --> 01:14:08,971
All right, done then.

1026
01:14:09,011 --> 01:14:10,672
What else do we have here?

1027
01:14:10,712 --> 01:14:13,476
Some salmon, Mr. Taft?

1028
01:14:22,257 --> 01:14:24,817
It's, um...

1029
01:14:24,860 --> 01:14:27,192
Bon appetit.

1030
01:14:29,998 --> 01:14:31,693
The minister
from the Baptist church

1031
01:14:31,733 --> 01:14:34,566
in, I think it's
Canton, North Carolina--

1032
01:14:34,603 --> 01:14:37,265
Reverend Washington?
I love that man.

1033
01:14:37,306 --> 01:14:38,705
What does--
what does he want?

1034
01:14:38,740 --> 01:14:40,731
Well, apparently there was
a fire at his church.

1035
01:14:40,776 --> 01:14:43,609
They've raised $1 million
but they need another $600,000.

1036
01:14:43,645 --> 01:14:46,739
Give him whatever he wants
and I'll write a personal note.

1037
01:14:46,782 --> 01:14:48,841
What else?

1038
01:14:51,787 --> 01:14:54,119
What else do we have?

1039
01:14:54,156 --> 01:14:57,091
You're not hungry, Mr. Taft?

1040
01:14:57,125 --> 01:14:59,923
Um...

1041
01:14:59,962 --> 01:15:01,122
no.

1042
01:15:01,163 --> 01:15:03,461
How about a nice glass
of Peu Chimay?

1043
01:15:03,499 --> 01:15:06,559
No, thank you.
I never drink when I'm driving.

1044
01:15:06,602 --> 01:15:10,732
Lafferty, why don't you
fix Mr. Taft some...

1045
01:15:10,772 --> 01:15:12,831
coffee?

1046
01:15:12,875 --> 01:15:15,605
All right. Sure.

1047
01:15:15,644 --> 01:15:18,511
- Peu Chimay, ma'am?
- No, just some coffee.

1048
01:15:18,547 --> 01:15:21,448
What's this now?

1049
01:15:21,483 --> 01:15:24,281
- The literacy program.
- Oh yes, the literacy program.

1050
01:15:24,319 --> 01:15:26,981
- How are they doing?
- Doing great work.

1051
01:15:27,022 --> 01:15:31,584
You know, I'm confused
because I saw this State Senate report

1052
01:15:31,627 --> 01:15:34,562
that made it seem
as if there were some problems.

1053
01:15:35,797 --> 01:15:37,162
Oh.

1054
01:15:37,199 --> 01:15:39,167
You know,
when I first came to America

1055
01:15:39,201 --> 01:15:40,862
I could hardly
write my own name.

1056
01:15:40,903 --> 01:15:43,872
And then I took one
of those literacy programs,

1057
01:15:43,906 --> 01:15:46,067
and now look at me.

1058
01:16:25,347 --> 01:16:27,611
Fuck.

1059
01:16:43,498 --> 01:16:45,466
No one wanted to tell you.

1060
01:16:45,500 --> 01:16:47,468
We know how fond
you are of him.

1061
01:16:47,502 --> 01:16:51,495
Petrus '89, '90, '91-- all gone.

1062
01:16:51,540 --> 01:16:52,939
Christ.

1063
01:16:52,975 --> 01:16:55,102
Chateau Margaux '86,

1064
01:16:55,143 --> 01:16:57,873
only the Premier Grand Cru.

1065
01:16:57,913 --> 01:17:01,508
Well, he has excellent taste,
you got to hand him that.

1066
01:17:01,550 --> 01:17:04,383
All the sherry--
maybe 100 bottles.

1067
01:17:04,419 --> 01:17:06,216
Jesus.

1068
01:17:06,254 --> 01:17:08,552
You want me to
do something about this?

1069
01:17:15,964 --> 01:17:19,127
Pack your bags.
You're fired.

1070
01:17:19,167 --> 01:17:22,000
Dear Miss Duke,

1071
01:17:22,037 --> 01:17:26,030
as always, I found it difficult
getting used to being in rehab.

1072
01:17:26,074 --> 01:17:29,737
But I have managed
to stay dry for two weeks now

1073
01:17:29,778 --> 01:17:33,145
and I think it's time
I came home.

1074
01:17:35,283 --> 01:17:37,046
Dear Lafferty,

1075
01:17:37,085 --> 01:17:39,110
I don't believe people
should be punished

1076
01:17:39,154 --> 01:17:41,486
because they suffer
from an illness.

1077
01:17:41,523 --> 01:17:45,983
That is why I haven't fired you,
as I probably should have.

1078
01:17:46,028 --> 01:17:50,431
But I'm not yet ready to have you back
as a trusted member of my household.

1079
01:17:50,465 --> 01:17:53,730
You will stay in rehab until
I am ready to forgive you.

1080
01:18:00,108 --> 01:18:02,269
Doris.

1081
01:18:02,310 --> 01:18:04,471
Doris, you okay?

1082
01:18:06,081 --> 01:18:08,447
Doris, you okay?

1083
01:18:08,483 --> 01:18:10,451
Doris?

1084
01:18:11,720 --> 01:18:12,880
Doris?

1085
01:18:21,163 --> 01:18:24,291
Dr. Armenza, please report
to lCU, STAT.

1086
01:18:24,332 --> 01:18:28,462
Dr. Armenza,
please report to lCU, STAT.

1087
01:18:30,305 --> 01:18:32,830
She's had a--
a sizeable stroke,

1088
01:18:32,874 --> 01:18:34,774
but I think she will get over that.

1089
01:18:34,810 --> 01:18:37,904
It will take time. She's gonna need
rehab and physical therapy.

1090
01:18:37,946 --> 01:18:40,506
But I am concerned about
her underlying condition,

1091
01:18:40,549 --> 01:18:42,141
which has always been
an issue,

1092
01:18:42,184 --> 01:18:45,278
in terms of her heart disease.
She's got a degenerative heart problem,

1093
01:18:45,320 --> 01:18:49,381
and also the liver issues.
Her liver function tests are not normal.

1094
01:18:49,424 --> 01:18:52,222
She'll need round-the-clock
care for now.

1095
01:19:59,694 --> 01:20:02,720
Here we go.

1096
01:20:03,732 --> 01:20:05,723
That's it.

1097
01:20:36,498 --> 01:20:39,262
What I did was unforgivable.

1098
01:20:44,039 --> 01:20:46,701
I'm so ashamed of myself.

1099
01:20:47,709 --> 01:20:49,438
You've taken me into your life,

1100
01:20:49,477 --> 01:20:51,570
you've been extremely
generous towards me.

1101
01:20:51,613 --> 01:20:54,104
I know I've let you down.

1102
01:20:54,149 --> 01:20:57,346
I can only say I'm deeply sorry.

1103
01:20:59,087 --> 01:21:02,147
I hope you can forgive me.

1104
01:21:02,190 --> 01:21:05,421
That's a good speech.
You learn it in rehab?

1105
01:21:10,232 --> 01:21:13,429
I wonder if you could help--

1106
01:21:13,468 --> 01:21:16,437
I'd very much like to keep my job.

1107
01:21:18,306 --> 01:21:20,171
Please.

1108
01:21:46,568 --> 01:21:50,026
Mr. Taft is calling
for Miss Duke, sir.

1109
01:21:51,139 --> 01:21:53,130
Okay.

1110
01:21:56,278 --> 01:21:58,269
Excuse me, Nancy.

1111
01:21:59,814 --> 01:22:01,714
- Mr. Taft.
- Lafferty.

1112
01:22:01,750 --> 01:22:03,411
I'm at the front gate, let me in.

1113
01:22:03,451 --> 01:22:06,147
I'm sorry, sir, Miss Duke's
not receiving visitors today, sir.

1114
01:22:06,187 --> 01:22:07,711
I want to talk to her.
Put her on.

1115
01:22:07,756 --> 01:22:09,121
She's not taking calls either, sir.

1116
01:22:09,157 --> 01:22:10,590
- Put her on.
- I'm sorry, sir.

1117
01:22:10,625 --> 01:22:12,354
I'm only following
Miss Duke's orders, sir.

1118
01:22:12,394 --> 01:22:14,521
- I know what you're up to...
- Mr. Taft,

1119
01:22:14,562 --> 01:22:17,087
Miss Duke appreciates your concern,
but her priority right now

1120
01:22:17,132 --> 01:22:19,498
- is to avoid all stress.
- Put her on right now.

1121
01:22:19,534 --> 01:22:22,230
And if you're truly her friend, you'll
respect her wish to be left alone.

1122
01:22:22,270 --> 01:22:24,033
- Lafferty, for crying out loud.
- Yes, sir.

1123
01:22:24,072 --> 01:22:26,165
- Thank you, sir, goodbye.
- This is ridiculous...

1124
01:22:45,093 --> 01:22:47,357
What are the police doing here?

1125
01:22:47,395 --> 01:22:51,729
We're just trying to
establish the facts, Doris.

1126
01:22:51,766 --> 01:22:53,893
I'm old, I have a bad heart,

1127
01:22:53,935 --> 01:22:56,130
my lungs are for shit,
end of story.

1128
01:22:56,171 --> 01:22:59,368
Did Mr. Lafferty try to control
your behavior in any way?

1129
01:22:59,407 --> 01:23:01,102
Well yes, he certainly has.

1130
01:23:01,142 --> 01:23:05,738
He's-- no visitors,
no phone calls, lights out at 9:00.

1131
01:23:05,780 --> 01:23:10,649
If devotion beyond the call
of duty were a crime,

1132
01:23:10,685 --> 01:23:13,449
he'd be a candidate
for Death Row.

1133
01:23:13,488 --> 01:23:17,219
That's what you call it?
"Devotion beyond the call of duty?"

1134
01:23:17,258 --> 01:23:19,818
Sorry to disappoint you, big guy.

1135
01:23:19,861 --> 01:23:22,125
Thank you, Miss Duke.

1136
01:23:29,104 --> 01:23:31,629
I'm sorry, Doris.

1137
01:23:31,673 --> 01:23:35,074
For all I knew, you might have been
locked in the attic like Baby Jane.

1138
01:23:35,110 --> 01:23:38,477
That's Blanche.
Baby Jane had the keys.

1139
01:23:38,513 --> 01:23:40,640
It worries me,
you being out here alone.

1140
01:23:40,682 --> 01:23:44,413
Let me get you proper care--
round-the-clock nursing.

1141
01:23:48,289 --> 01:23:51,850
- I'll think about it.
- They'll cluck around you

1142
01:23:51,893 --> 01:23:53,053
- like mother hens.
- Stop it.

1143
01:23:53,094 --> 01:23:55,062
They'll be patronizing you,
treating you like a child.

1144
01:23:55,096 --> 01:23:56,154
Blah blah
blah blah blah.

1145
01:23:56,197 --> 01:23:57,858
"It's time for
your bath now, Doris.

1146
01:23:57,899 --> 01:23:59,890
- Have we taken our medicine today?"
- Oh stop it.

1147
01:23:59,934 --> 01:24:01,868
- They'll drive you nuts.
- Just stop it.

1148
01:24:01,903 --> 01:24:04,497
- I'm still being punished, is that it?
- It's not about you, Lafferty.

1149
01:24:04,539 --> 01:24:06,734
I've tried to think of everything
I can to win back your trust.

1150
01:24:06,775 --> 01:24:08,402
I've ceased to exist
outside this house,

1151
01:24:08,443 --> 01:24:10,934
I've renounced my own life in order
to give you the care that you need.

1152
01:24:10,979 --> 01:24:13,209
- And now you discover it's not enough?
- The nurses are coming

1153
01:24:13,248 --> 01:24:15,409
- in the morning.
- It's the nurses or it's me.

1154
01:24:15,450 --> 01:24:17,748
- Oh, don't make idle threats.
- It's not an idle threat, ma'am.

1155
01:24:17,786 --> 01:24:19,845
Well then, stop it!

1156
01:24:22,290 --> 01:24:23,882
For God's sake.

1157
01:24:23,925 --> 01:24:25,893
Would you bring in the nurses
if it meant losing me?

1158
01:24:25,927 --> 01:24:28,191
- I won't be put on the spot.
- Answer me, please.

1159
01:24:28,229 --> 01:24:30,857
It's a simple question, ma'am.
Just yes or no.

1160
01:24:32,600 --> 01:24:36,001
I don't want you to go
if that's what you're asking.

1161
01:24:36,037 --> 01:24:38,597
So you would do
without the nurses?

1162
01:24:38,640 --> 01:24:40,972
I want you to stay.

1163
01:24:42,343 --> 01:24:44,573
In my current capacity?

1164
01:24:44,612 --> 01:24:47,274
Oh for God's sake, Lafferty.

1165
01:24:47,315 --> 01:24:51,081
I choose you above all others.

1166
01:24:53,521 --> 01:24:55,989
Mm.

1167
01:24:56,024 --> 01:24:58,117
Is that what you want?

1168
01:24:58,159 --> 01:25:01,890
And you are not to prevent
Mr. Taft from seeing me, ever.

1169
01:25:01,930 --> 01:25:03,921
- Agreed?
- Agreed.

1170
01:25:07,102 --> 01:25:10,162
We can still bring the nurses in
if you think it's necessary.

1171
01:25:10,205 --> 01:25:12,833
Oh no. You wanted me,
now you got me.

1172
01:25:34,028 --> 01:25:36,189
My daddy had pneumonia

1173
01:25:36,231 --> 01:25:40,031
and my mother sent away
all the maids

1174
01:25:40,068 --> 01:25:42,195
so she wouldn't have
any witnesses.

1175
01:25:42,237 --> 01:25:44,228
And then she stripped him naked

1176
01:25:44,272 --> 01:25:46,433
and opened up the windows,

1177
01:25:46,474 --> 01:25:50,843
because that's the way they do it
in Macon, Georgia, she says.

1178
01:25:50,879 --> 01:25:54,212
Of course,
this was New York.

1179
01:25:54,249 --> 01:25:57,275
The coldest October in history.

1180
01:25:58,987 --> 01:26:01,148
I was only allowed
to see him for a few minutes

1181
01:26:01,189 --> 01:26:03,180
every day after school.

1182
01:26:04,959 --> 01:26:08,053
You could see your breath
in the room.

1183
01:26:10,598 --> 01:26:14,193
The man froze to death
in his own home.

1184
01:26:14,235 --> 01:26:18,262
She thought that
she would get everything,

1185
01:26:18,306 --> 01:26:21,002
but my daddy knew what
kind of woman she was

1186
01:26:21,042 --> 01:26:23,875
and he left it all to me.

1187
01:26:33,421 --> 01:26:37,152
My father died
when I was three.

1188
01:26:44,432 --> 01:26:47,993
My-- my mother died
when I was eight.

1189
01:26:48,036 --> 01:26:49,526
Oh.

1190
01:26:49,571 --> 01:26:51,869
I was coming home
from school one day

1191
01:26:51,906 --> 01:26:55,467
and there was an ambulance there
at the end of our road.

1192
01:26:55,510 --> 01:26:59,344
A crowd was rubbernecking.

1193
01:26:59,380 --> 01:27:02,110
She was sitting up against a car.

1194
01:27:02,150 --> 01:27:05,210
It might have been the same one
that hit her, I don't know.

1195
01:27:05,253 --> 01:27:06,914
I thought she was all right

1196
01:27:06,955 --> 01:27:11,085
because there was no blood
or anything like that.

1197
01:27:11,125 --> 01:27:13,685
It looked like she was just
having a snooze there

1198
01:27:13,728 --> 01:27:15,696
in the middle of the road.

1199
01:27:15,730 --> 01:27:19,564
Her shopping was scattered
all about...

1200
01:27:22,003 --> 01:27:25,666
porridge oats
and pink custard powder.

1201
01:27:28,042 --> 01:27:30,943
The only family I had
after that was an aunt

1202
01:27:30,979 --> 01:27:33,209
in Philadelphia.

1203
01:27:36,918 --> 01:27:39,011
Fate.

1204
01:27:47,228 --> 01:27:50,925
Here, let me give you
a hand with that, Miss Duke.

1205
01:27:50,965 --> 01:27:53,092
You just missed it...

1206
01:27:53,134 --> 01:27:55,125
a bit here.

1207
01:27:58,406 --> 01:28:00,636
There, take a look.

1208
01:28:05,813 --> 01:28:08,043
I need more eyes.

1209
01:28:08,082 --> 01:28:10,243
Sure.

1210
01:28:26,934 --> 01:28:29,903
That's okay.
Let's do the other side.

1211
01:28:29,937 --> 01:28:33,896
You know, when you do it,
you should start from the base

1212
01:28:33,941 --> 01:28:36,876
to the tip. Try it on you.

1213
01:28:40,448 --> 01:28:42,780
- From the base to the tip?
- Yeah.

1214
01:28:44,185 --> 01:28:47,018
- Okay, like that?
- Mm.

1215
01:28:47,055 --> 01:28:49,046
Yeah.

1216
01:29:07,809 --> 01:29:10,676
Good evening, Nancy.

1217
01:29:28,396 --> 01:29:30,159
- Will that be all, Miss Du--
- Oh stop it.

1218
01:29:30,198 --> 01:29:32,189
Just sit down.

1219
01:29:50,218 --> 01:29:52,778
Happy birthday, Miss Duke.

1220
01:30:06,067 --> 01:30:09,833
I'm afraid this is not one of your more
glamorous birthday parties.

1221
01:30:09,871 --> 01:30:12,101
Oh, I've had much worse.

1222
01:30:12,140 --> 01:30:15,439
Perhaps you'll be up
to having a party again next year.

1223
01:30:17,712 --> 01:30:19,771
Lafferty, there are
a couple of things

1224
01:30:19,814 --> 01:30:22,112
I want you to do for me
when I'm gone.

1225
01:30:22,150 --> 01:30:23,674
Do we have to talk
about that now?

1226
01:30:23,718 --> 01:30:26,118
- My bed socks, for instance.
- Bed socks?

1227
01:30:26,154 --> 01:30:29,055
Yes, I sometimes wear
bed socks when I sleep.

1228
01:30:29,090 --> 01:30:31,115
I've done so since
I was a little girl,

1229
01:30:31,159 --> 01:30:34,856
and if I should be
wearing my bed socks

1230
01:30:34,896 --> 01:30:36,955
when I fall off the twig,

1231
01:30:36,998 --> 01:30:39,831
I would like you to please

1232
01:30:39,867 --> 01:30:42,392
remove them from my feet

1233
01:30:42,437 --> 01:30:44,632
before the coroner gets there.

1234
01:30:44,672 --> 01:30:47,300
I don't want to look
like a complete idiot.

1235
01:30:47,341 --> 01:30:48,808
Yes, sure.

1236
01:30:48,843 --> 01:30:50,970
No fancy speeches.

1237
01:30:51,012 --> 01:30:52,604
No press.

1238
01:30:52,647 --> 01:30:55,514
And I would like you to...

1239
01:30:55,550 --> 01:30:58,348
dress me in something casual.

1240
01:30:58,386 --> 01:31:00,354
Life is a journey, after all,

1241
01:31:00,388 --> 01:31:03,255
and I refuse to go into that box
wearing an evening gown

